1
00:00:00,640 --> 00:00:02,430
Previously on Fairy Tail:

2
00:00:02,430 --> 00:00:05,650
To visit someone named Daphne who 
was said to have met a dragon,

3
00:00:05,650 --> 00:00:08,230
we came to a traveler's inn named "Rise".

4
00:00:08,230 --> 00:00:10,070
I knew I had a bad feeling about this.

5
00:00:10,070 --> 00:00:13,230
So of course, we fell right into the 
trap, and are completely shut in!

6
00:00:13,230 --> 00:00:14,490
Yes-yes-yes...

7
00:00:14,490 --> 00:00:16,570
I've been waiting for you, Dragon Slayer.

8
00:00:16,570 --> 00:00:19,200
So, what are you doing here, Gray?

9
00:01:59,400 --> 00:02:00,610
Gray-san?

10
00:02:00,610 --> 00:02:02,220
What's wrong with you, Gray?

11
00:02:02,220 --> 00:02:04,300
Stand back, Wendy.

12
00:02:05,470 --> 00:02:06,980
He's being serious.

13
00:02:06,980 --> 00:02:08,700
Gray, what's wrong?

14
00:02:08,700 --> 00:02:10,070
Do you have a stomachache?

15
00:02:10,070 --> 00:02:11,710
That's obviously not the problem!

16
00:02:11,710 --> 00:02:12,440
Gray-san!

17
00:02:12,440 --> 00:02:14,440
Ice Make Lance!

18
00:02:17,890 --> 00:02:19,560
Natsu-san! Gray-san!

19
00:02:19,560 --> 00:02:20,950
What's going on?

20
00:02:21,900 --> 00:02:24,700
Gray! Why are you attacking Natsu?

21
00:02:26,800 --> 00:02:28,040
Yes-yes-yes...

22
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:29,730
I bet you are surprised.

23
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:32,930
But you have no time to 
stand there slack-jawed.

24
00:02:32,930 --> 00:02:36,380
Gray Fullbuster, finish them off!

25
00:02:36,380 --> 00:02:37,850
I heard ya!

26
00:02:37,850 --> 00:02:41,040
What do you think you're doing, seriously?

27
00:02:41,040 --> 00:02:43,030
Nothin' at all.

28
00:02:43,030 --> 00:02:46,060
Just wiping you out, is all!

29
00:02:47,680 --> 00:02:49,940
Stop it, Gray-san!

30
00:02:49,940 --> 00:02:53,190
Wait, isn't he a fake?

31
00:02:53,190 --> 00:02:54,610
Something similar happened before.

32
00:02:54,610 --> 00:02:56,050
That's right!

33
00:02:56,050 --> 00:02:58,570
There's something different 
about Gray this time...

34
00:02:58,570 --> 00:02:59,880
Something different?

35
00:02:59,880 --> 00:03:01,050
Like what?

36
00:03:01,050 --> 00:03:03,110
Um...

37
00:03:05,510 --> 00:03:08,360
Let's do this for real already, Natsu.

38
00:03:08,650 --> 00:03:09,600
He stripped.

39
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,510
He really is Gray!

40
00:03:11,510 --> 00:03:12,710
That's what it was?

41
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,850
Natsu vs. Gray!!

42
00:03:19,380 --> 00:03:22,240
You bastard... You're seriously going for it?

43
00:03:22,240 --> 00:03:23,590
Here I come, Natsu.

44
00:03:23,590 --> 00:03:26,180
Ice Make Battle Axe!

45
00:03:26,180 --> 00:03:27,760
Roar of the Fire Dragon!

46
00:03:34,950 --> 00:03:36,990
Yes-yes, that's the way.

47
00:03:36,990 --> 00:03:39,150
He's not a fake, absolutely not.

48
00:03:39,150 --> 00:03:43,450
He is the honest to goodness 
Gray Fullbuster, in the flesh!

49
00:03:45,710 --> 00:03:49,460
And just so you know, I'm not 
controlling him using magic!

50
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:51,870
He is doing this of his own free will!

51
00:03:53,750 --> 00:03:55,460
You don't need to tell me that.

52
00:03:56,290 --> 00:04:00,710
No one's punches could piss me off 
the same way as the real Gray's!

53
00:04:00,960 --> 00:04:05,430
You're tellin' me you <i>let</i> me 
punch you as some sort of test?

54
00:04:07,070 --> 00:04:09,140
Talons of the Fire Dragon!

55
00:04:11,180 --> 00:04:12,600
Hold it, buddy!

56
00:04:13,060 --> 00:04:14,370
Natsu!

57
00:04:14,370 --> 00:04:15,940
Overdoing it, as always.

58
00:04:19,900 --> 00:04:21,540
That enough?

59
00:04:21,540 --> 00:04:23,700
Explain what's going on already.

60
00:04:23,700 --> 00:04:25,700
What the hell are you thinking, Gray?

61
00:04:25,700 --> 00:04:27,430
A city without sound.

62
00:04:27,700 --> 00:04:30,690
Huh? A city without sound?

63
00:04:30,690 --> 00:04:31,790
What are you talking about?

64
00:04:31,790 --> 00:04:33,960
You wouldn't understand.

65
00:04:33,960 --> 00:04:36,450
But it doesn't matter anyway!

66
00:04:36,450 --> 00:04:38,290
Just die already!

67
00:04:40,840 --> 00:04:43,920
Wow... Both of their powers are about equal.

68
00:04:43,920 --> 00:04:46,100
This is no time to be impressed!

69
00:04:46,100 --> 00:04:46,830
Aye...

70
00:04:46,830 --> 00:04:48,670
What in the world is this?

71
00:04:48,670 --> 00:04:50,490
Why is Gray-san doing this?

72
00:04:50,840 --> 00:04:55,330
Gray Fullbuster volunteered 
to assist me of his own will.

73
00:04:55,330 --> 00:04:56,800
Of his own will?

74
00:04:56,800 --> 00:04:59,980
I came to Magnolia about 10 days ago.

75
00:04:59,980 --> 00:05:03,650
When I went to investigate the 
origins of Natsu Dragneel,

76
00:05:05,020 --> 00:05:12,220
I happened upon Gray Fullbuster, who took 
interest in my story, and offered to assist me, see.

77
00:05:12,870 --> 00:05:14,970
Right now, he's my partner!

78
00:05:15,370 --> 00:05:17,980
He's a complete traitor!

79
00:05:17,980 --> 00:05:20,470
But... I can't believe that!

80
00:05:20,470 --> 00:05:24,050
That means that Gray and Daphne really do...

81
00:05:24,590 --> 00:05:26,780
...lllllike each other!

82
00:05:27,070 --> 00:05:27,930
Could be.

83
00:05:27,930 --> 00:05:29,150
She didn't deny it!

84
00:05:29,150 --> 00:05:31,040
Whoa! Juvia ain't gonna let this stand!

85
00:05:31,040 --> 00:05:32,850
It's gonna be a bloodbath!

86
00:05:32,850 --> 00:05:34,700
Honestly, you are so annoying!

87
00:05:34,700 --> 00:05:37,520
Stop butting into every conversation!

88
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,580
I'm sorry...

89
00:05:39,910 --> 00:05:43,730
What is the "city without sound" 
that Gray-san is talking about?

90
00:05:43,730 --> 00:05:46,250
Why were you investigating Natsu-san exactly?

91
00:05:46,250 --> 00:05:47,340
Yes-yes!

92
00:05:47,340 --> 00:05:48,440
Hold all questions for later.

93
00:05:48,440 --> 00:05:50,300
Why don't you have a snack, yes?

94
00:05:50,300 --> 00:05:51,950
Don't be silly!

95
00:05:51,950 --> 00:05:53,200
Now is not the time!

96
00:05:53,200 --> 00:05:55,120
Well, maybe just one more...

97
00:05:55,940 --> 00:05:58,050
Don't eat them!

98
00:05:59,580 --> 00:06:01,400
Hot!!

99
00:06:01,400 --> 00:06:03,040
That's the spicy flavor.

100
00:06:03,040 --> 00:06:04,700
Would you like one?

101
00:06:07,710 --> 00:06:09,980
What is with her?

102
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:13,440
I'm gettin' fired up!

103
00:06:13,440 --> 00:06:16,180
If you're being serious, then so will I!

104
00:06:16,550 --> 00:06:19,730
I'll beat the reason for this outta you!

105
00:06:26,290 --> 00:06:27,400
He's late!

106
00:06:27,400 --> 00:06:29,580
What is Natsu doing?

107
00:06:29,860 --> 00:06:32,420
He should have returned by now.

108
00:06:32,420 --> 00:06:35,040
He only went to ask about dragons, after all.

109
00:06:35,040 --> 00:06:36,710
Definitely taking too long for that.

110
00:06:36,710 --> 00:06:39,240
I think you should calm down, Erza.

111
00:06:39,240 --> 00:06:42,130
He's probably just taking 
his time, that's all.

112
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:46,770
No. He had Wendy with him, so it's 
strange for him to be this late.

113
00:06:46,770 --> 00:06:48,800
It ain't like Natsu.

114
00:06:48,800 --> 00:06:52,920
Draggin' a little girl around 
town all night ain't Manly!

115
00:06:52,920 --> 00:06:56,580
I'm also worried about the thing 
that suddenly attacked me today.

116
00:06:56,890 --> 00:06:58,610
What if it also attacked Natsu and Wendy?

117
00:06:58,610 --> 00:07:00,980
Juvia is worried about Gray-sama!

118
00:07:01,510 --> 00:07:06,880
Juvia feels unease in her heart, wondering 
if something has happened to him!

119
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,700
And I think you're just worryin' too much.

120
00:07:09,700 --> 00:07:12,410
He might've just gone straight home.

121
00:07:12,660 --> 00:07:16,100
The intuition of a woman 
in love is never wrong!

122
00:07:16,100 --> 00:07:18,490
Right, sure! Don't look at me like that!

123
00:07:18,490 --> 00:07:20,580
Don't take it so seriously!

124
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:21,750
We'll go search for him.

125
00:07:21,750 --> 00:07:22,990
Lucy, come with me.

126
00:07:22,990 --> 00:07:23,900
Okay.

127
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,700
Juvia will come as well.

128
00:07:25,700 --> 00:07:27,010
Take me with you, too.

129
00:07:27,010 --> 00:07:29,980
No, I want you to stand by here.

130
00:07:29,980 --> 00:07:32,010
We don't want to leave 
the guild short-handed.

131
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:35,130
Be careful out there, Erza, Lucy.

132
00:07:45,770 --> 00:07:48,020
Ice Make Shield!

133
00:07:48,020 --> 00:07:50,430
Talons of the Fire Dragon!

134
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:55,170
Ice Make Floor!

135
00:08:02,390 --> 00:08:03,710
Take that!

136
00:08:03,710 --> 00:08:06,380
Take this, you!

137
00:08:07,740 --> 00:08:09,460
Ice Cannon!

138
00:08:10,960 --> 00:08:15,370
Wing Slash of the Fire Dragon!

139
00:08:19,900 --> 00:08:21,000
Wow...

140
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:23,020
Neither of their attacks can finish it!

141
00:08:23,020 --> 00:08:26,580
At this rate, they'll both use 
up their energy and collapse!

142
00:08:26,580 --> 00:08:28,690
You can do it, Natsu!

143
00:08:28,960 --> 00:08:31,500
Flaming Elbow of the Fire Dragon!

144
00:08:37,490 --> 00:08:38,900
A pool!

145
00:08:38,900 --> 00:08:40,900
Wait, this isn't good.

146
00:08:41,810 --> 00:08:43,380
This'll do!

147
00:08:44,120 --> 00:08:45,770
Ice Make...

148
00:08:46,290 --> 00:08:47,540
...Prison!

149
00:08:49,300 --> 00:08:50,750
Hey, you!

150
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:52,200
No fair!

151
00:08:52,200 --> 00:08:53,640
Let me out!

152
00:08:54,470 --> 00:08:59,290
Yes-yes... He used the water from 
the pool and made a giant cage, yes?

153
00:08:59,290 --> 00:09:01,430
You've got a decent head 
on your shoulders there.

154
00:09:01,430 --> 00:09:03,350
Look at you now, heh.

155
00:09:03,350 --> 00:09:05,490
I'm not some animal!

156
00:09:05,490 --> 00:09:07,730
Roar of the Fire Dragon!

157
00:09:10,750 --> 00:09:12,480
Damn it! I can't see!

158
00:09:12,780 --> 00:09:14,690
You fell for it, Natsu!

159
00:09:14,690 --> 00:09:15,240
Crap!

160
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,200
Ice Make Lance!

161
00:09:21,070 --> 00:09:24,120
I always planned on settling 
things with you one day.

162
00:09:25,150 --> 00:09:26,830
And today's the day!

163
00:09:27,620 --> 00:09:29,510
You bastard...

164
00:09:29,510 --> 00:09:31,090
Fine by me!

165
00:09:31,090 --> 00:09:32,540
Stop your babbling!

166
00:09:33,110 --> 00:09:36,370
You're the one who needs to shut it!

167
00:09:39,940 --> 00:09:40,850
They're on the first floor!

168
00:09:40,850 --> 00:09:41,830
Let's go!

169
00:09:41,830 --> 00:09:42,860
Right!

170
00:09:43,670 --> 00:09:45,190
Natsu!

171
00:09:45,190 --> 00:09:46,600
Where are you?

172
00:09:46,840 --> 00:09:51,200
At this rate, I'll need to stop the two 
of them with my Roar of the Sky Dragon!

173
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:56,030
But if you use it in such a confined space, 
you might seriously injure everyone!

174
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:59,000
Okay, I'll go call for help!

175
00:09:59,000 --> 00:10:00,490
Wait, Happy!

176
00:10:02,660 --> 00:10:04,630
You never learn, do you?

177
00:10:04,870 --> 00:10:07,270
Yes-yes... Resistance is futile, you know.

178
00:10:07,270 --> 00:10:10,080
You cannot escape from this building.

179
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:10,840
That's it!

180
00:10:10,840 --> 00:10:12,570
If I can beat her...

181
00:10:12,570 --> 00:10:15,550
This one is brightly colored 
vegetable-flavored.

182
00:10:17,090 --> 00:10:19,550
Eww!

183
00:10:19,550 --> 00:10:21,870
Escaping isn't going to work.

184
00:10:21,870 --> 00:10:24,850
After all, this inn is an illusion I created.

185
00:10:25,140 --> 00:10:26,940
An illusionary inn?

186
00:10:26,940 --> 00:10:27,780
That's right.

187
00:10:27,780 --> 00:10:31,770
My magic, Concealment Magic, 
hides people and things.

188
00:10:31,770 --> 00:10:35,940
This inn was created with the 
Concealment Magic "Hidden Cage".

189
00:10:35,940 --> 00:10:38,460
In other words, it's a building 
that doesn't actually exist!

190
00:10:40,500 --> 00:10:43,150
Oh? Looks like your friends 
came to pick you up.

191
00:10:46,700 --> 00:10:49,280
Erza-san! Lucy-san!

192
00:10:49,280 --> 00:10:51,420
We're up here!

193
00:10:53,930 --> 00:10:57,640
The inn Gray was talking about 
should have been around here...

194
00:10:57,910 --> 00:10:59,840
Be careful, Lucy.

195
00:11:01,420 --> 00:11:02,900
I can smell a beast.

196
00:11:10,080 --> 00:11:12,260
W-What's that thing?

197
00:11:12,940 --> 00:11:14,480
The sneak-attacker.

198
00:11:14,850 --> 00:11:16,450
I had a feeling it would show up.

199
00:11:25,870 --> 00:11:27,790
Lucy, stand back.

200
00:11:28,240 --> 00:11:29,550
Be careful!

201
00:11:35,860 --> 00:11:37,570
What is your purpose?

202
00:11:37,930 --> 00:11:40,460
Did you also attack Natsu and Wendy?

203
00:11:40,460 --> 00:11:41,590
Answer me!

204
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:51,290
Erza!

205
00:11:51,290 --> 00:11:52,270
Okay!

206
00:11:53,390 --> 00:11:55,690
Gate of the Maiden, I open thee!

207
00:11:56,150 --> 00:11:57,220
Virgo!

208
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:02,290
An impressive comedic reaction, Princess.

209
00:12:02,290 --> 00:12:04,150
I haven't said anything yet!

210
00:12:04,400 --> 00:12:05,820
Thank you, like that.

211
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:08,440
Anyway, save Erza!

212
00:12:08,440 --> 00:12:09,750
As you wish.

213
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:13,750
Princess, watch out.

214
00:12:19,600 --> 00:12:21,210
There's more than one of you?

215
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:24,380
Leave this to me, Princess.

216
00:12:25,260 --> 00:12:27,360
Planning to catch it off guard?

217
00:12:27,360 --> 00:12:28,960
I'm counting on you, Virgo!

218
00:12:30,260 --> 00:12:32,420
The same ability as Virgo?!

219
00:12:34,620 --> 00:12:35,590
Where is the enemy?

220
00:12:44,050 --> 00:12:46,780
It has no grace in its hole digging.

221
00:12:48,320 --> 00:12:49,950
Come on out.

222
00:12:49,950 --> 00:12:51,740
I will show you the proper way to dig a hole.

223
00:12:55,490 --> 00:12:57,710
It seems your magic power 
has increased somewhat.

224
00:12:58,420 --> 00:12:59,970
Spica Lock!

225
00:13:08,850 --> 00:13:10,450
It is a powerful opponent, Princess.

226
00:13:10,450 --> 00:13:12,900
Don't push yourself. Rest a little while.

227
00:13:12,900 --> 00:13:14,360
I apologize.

228
00:13:16,830 --> 00:13:18,340
In that case...

229
00:13:20,420 --> 00:13:22,650
Long time no see, Lucy.

230
00:13:22,650 --> 00:13:25,280
I'm countin' on you again. 
Can you handle it, Loke?

231
00:13:25,280 --> 00:13:27,690
You don't need to ask.

232
00:13:27,690 --> 00:13:30,300
I am the leader of the 12 Zodiacs.

233
00:13:30,300 --> 00:13:34,790
I will pay back the favor you did me 
by taking in Aries and the others.

234
00:13:40,750 --> 00:13:42,470
A different one, again?

235
00:13:42,470 --> 00:13:47,140
I'd like to say it's just a different 
body, but that doesn't seem the case.

236
00:13:50,650 --> 00:13:51,980
Interesting!

237
00:13:51,980 --> 00:13:55,350
You intend to fight a spirit specializing 
in fighting with brute power?

238
00:13:57,180 --> 00:13:59,190
In just one instant...

239
00:13:59,190 --> 00:14:01,560
It raised its magic power?

240
00:14:01,800 --> 00:14:04,990
Are these things mimicking us?

241
00:14:12,660 --> 00:14:15,420
Lucy-san! Erza-san!

242
00:14:15,420 --> 00:14:18,530
It doesn't seem like they 
can see us from over there.

243
00:14:20,020 --> 00:14:22,750
Are you in league with 
those spiky-headed things?

244
00:14:22,750 --> 00:14:24,910
Yes-yes... Quite correct.

245
00:14:24,910 --> 00:14:29,870
I have various types of artificial 
life forms stored within this place.

246
00:14:29,870 --> 00:14:31,860
Artificial life forms?

247
00:14:31,860 --> 00:14:33,570
Some type of golem, right?

248
00:14:33,570 --> 00:14:37,790
And I made them with a system 
where they automatically adapt

249
00:14:37,790 --> 00:14:40,110
to match the attributes of their opponent.

250
00:14:40,460 --> 00:14:42,640
I was thinking that along 
with Natsu Dragneel,

251
00:14:42,640 --> 00:14:46,280
I could gather information 
about a variety of wizards.

252
00:14:46,280 --> 00:14:48,530
And what are you planning by that?

253
00:14:49,100 --> 00:14:51,790
You'll just have to stay tuned.

254
00:14:51,790 --> 00:14:57,120
The more data I gather, the 
more interesting it'll be.

255
00:15:00,110 --> 00:15:00,870
Whoa there.

256
00:15:01,400 --> 00:15:02,920
Looks like we're getting 
to the end of the battle.

257
00:15:07,960 --> 00:15:11,800
Sheesh, you're one majorly 
tough bastard, you know that?

258
00:15:11,800 --> 00:15:14,770
That's my line, damn it.

259
00:15:14,770 --> 00:15:16,720
You can do it, Natsu!

260
00:15:16,990 --> 00:15:20,180
Yes-yes-yes... That's enough talking.

261
00:15:20,180 --> 00:15:23,520
It's about time, Gray Fullbuster!

262
00:15:23,520 --> 00:15:25,610
No need to tell me that!

263
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:28,400
Bring it!

264
00:15:28,400 --> 00:15:31,020
Natsu!

265
00:15:34,910 --> 00:15:37,460
Gray!

266
00:15:43,470 --> 00:15:45,030
Natsu won!

267
00:15:45,030 --> 00:15:47,130
He isn't called the Salamander for nothing.

268
00:15:49,210 --> 00:15:50,980
Indeed, impressive.

269
00:15:53,900 --> 00:15:57,130
How'd you like that? I win, Gray.

270
00:15:58,850 --> 00:15:59,610
Gray?

271
00:16:00,350 --> 00:16:04,130
My bad! I hit you somewhere I shouldn't?

272
00:16:04,130 --> 00:16:05,620
Just kiddin'...

273
00:16:06,250 --> 00:16:08,940
Hey, how long are you gonna play...

274
00:16:09,600 --> 00:16:11,400
My feet are freezing!

275
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,690
See?

276
00:16:13,370 --> 00:16:15,280
You're too naïve.

277
00:16:15,990 --> 00:16:17,230
Yes-yes-yes...

278
00:16:17,230 --> 00:16:18,680
Good work.

279
00:16:19,160 --> 00:16:20,830
Hidden Darkness!

280
00:16:21,600 --> 00:16:24,480
What the heck?!

281
00:16:29,260 --> 00:16:31,830
Excellent work, Gray Fullbuster.

282
00:16:32,350 --> 00:16:34,530
You get high marks as my assistant.

283
00:16:34,530 --> 00:16:35,760
Thanks.

284
00:16:35,760 --> 00:16:37,780
Took a bit of work, though.

285
00:16:39,100 --> 00:16:40,670
Natsu!

286
00:16:40,670 --> 00:16:41,560
Natsu-san!

287
00:16:41,960 --> 00:16:46,320
You planned on leading us here 
from the start, didn't you?

288
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:49,230
Yeah. Plan worked like a charm, I think.

289
00:16:49,230 --> 00:16:52,280
Don't talk so big when you 
just lost the real fight!

290
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:55,480
I'll throw you in with 'im!

291
00:16:58,240 --> 00:16:59,490
Yes-yes.

292
00:16:59,490 --> 00:17:01,200
Please refrain from doing that.

293
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:05,160
After finally capturing Salamander, 
don't mix in anything unnecessary.

294
00:17:06,000 --> 00:17:08,290
I think I've been dissed.

295
00:17:08,550 --> 00:17:11,030
Was that your goal?

296
00:17:11,510 --> 00:17:12,390
Yes.

297
00:17:12,640 --> 00:17:16,280
With this, my research will be complete.

298
00:17:17,890 --> 00:17:20,020
Gray! Happy!

299
00:17:20,340 --> 00:17:22,870
Wendy! Carla!

300
00:17:33,880 --> 00:17:35,510
A dragon's egg!

301
00:17:39,340 --> 00:17:40,700
That voice...

302
00:17:42,220 --> 00:17:43,740
Igneel, is that you?

303
00:17:43,740 --> 00:17:46,080
Wait for me! Answer me!

304
00:17:46,580 --> 00:17:48,630
Igneel!

305
00:17:51,550 --> 00:17:53,070
Igneel...

306
00:18:01,510 --> 00:18:02,510
Ingeel.

307
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,140
A dragon's egg.

308
00:18:05,490 --> 00:18:06,940
A city without sound.

309
00:18:07,910 --> 00:18:10,150
That's it! I remember!

310
00:18:15,980 --> 00:18:17,440
Natsu!

311
00:18:20,060 --> 00:18:21,230
What?

312
00:18:21,230 --> 00:18:23,190
The real fun starts now.

313
00:18:28,830 --> 00:18:33,880
It looks like you have some trick 
to match any ability I use.

314
00:18:34,570 --> 00:18:36,020
But in that case...

315
00:18:36,020 --> 00:18:37,180
Requip!

316
00:18:37,580 --> 00:18:39,250
Adamantine Armor!

317
00:18:43,150 --> 00:18:44,720
And requip once again!

318
00:18:53,940 --> 00:18:59,200
You may have the same ability, but no 
one is faster at requipping than I.

319
00:18:59,200 --> 00:19:02,280
The choice of weapons and armor is 
something only experience can bring.

320
00:19:03,950 --> 00:19:06,240
A fake will never be anything but a fake.

321
00:19:11,570 --> 00:19:13,780
This is getting us nowhere.

322
00:19:13,780 --> 00:19:15,980
If the opponent mimics us, then...

323
00:19:16,210 --> 00:19:17,370
That's it!

324
00:19:17,370 --> 00:19:18,700
I did this before once!

325
00:19:18,700 --> 00:19:20,240
I'll leave the rest to you.

326
00:19:20,240 --> 00:19:21,810
I pray for your victory.

327
00:19:24,110 --> 00:19:26,680
Gate of Canis Minor, I open thee!

328
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:27,600
Nicolas!

329
00:19:57,880 --> 00:20:00,260
All right! This is working perfectly!

330
00:20:00,520 --> 00:20:01,530
I think...

331
00:20:15,750 --> 00:20:16,960
Good work.

332
00:20:16,960 --> 00:20:18,870
You sure gave it your all.

333
00:20:31,080 --> 00:20:32,950
Yes-yes-yes-yes!

334
00:20:32,950 --> 00:20:35,080
Lift Concealment Magic!

335
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:37,460
Lacrima core, stand by for operation!

336
00:20:37,460 --> 00:20:39,880
Unlock all joints!

337
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:43,030
Neurotransmission lacrima 
sensitivity, all green!

338
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:48,530
All impurities other than 
Salamander, get out already!

339
00:20:50,180 --> 00:20:51,770
Yes-yes-yes-yes!

340
00:20:51,770 --> 00:20:55,980
Now, begin absorption of 
Salamander's magic power!

341
00:21:03,440 --> 00:21:07,600
Dragonoid... activate!

342
00:21:10,250 --> 00:21:11,430
Dragonoid?

343
00:21:11,800 --> 00:21:14,660
Absorb Salamander's magic power?

344
00:21:15,350 --> 00:21:16,760
Natsu!

345
00:21:22,590 --> 00:21:24,530
It's so loud!

346
00:21:25,050 --> 00:21:26,310
Yes-yes-yes...

347
00:21:26,310 --> 00:21:28,430
Things are starting off quite well.

348
00:21:28,430 --> 00:21:30,060
Take a look!

349
00:21:30,060 --> 00:21:32,900
This is the artificial dragon I invented!

350
00:21:32,900 --> 00:21:34,700
I call it a Dragonoid!

351
00:21:34,700 --> 00:21:39,060
I'm taking Salamander's magic power 
and unveiling it for all to see!

352
00:21:39,060 --> 00:21:40,980
Natsu's magic power?

353
00:21:41,480 --> 00:21:43,150
Lucy-san!

354
00:21:43,150 --> 00:21:44,780
Erza-san!

355
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:46,220
It's you!

356
00:21:46,220 --> 00:21:47,360
You're safe?

357
00:21:47,360 --> 00:21:49,320
We're in big trouble!

358
00:21:49,320 --> 00:21:51,230
What in the world is happening?

359
00:21:51,230 --> 00:21:52,280
Where's Natsu?

360
00:21:52,280 --> 00:21:54,450
He's been captured!

361
00:21:54,450 --> 00:21:58,470
Gray joined forces with this Daphne 
person and set a trap for Natsu!

362
00:21:58,470 --> 00:21:59,670
Gray did?

363
00:22:00,030 --> 00:22:02,020
He's not being controlled.

364
00:22:02,020 --> 00:22:03,600
She said it was of his own free will.

365
00:22:04,020 --> 00:22:06,510
We don't really understand ourselves.

366
00:22:07,270 --> 00:22:08,200
Gray!

367
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:58,940
Happy, what is this weird thing?

368
00:23:58,940 --> 00:24:03,190
It's called a Dragonoid, 
and it's a man-made dragon.

369
00:24:03,190 --> 00:24:05,040
Oh, so it's just a fake?

370
00:24:05,040 --> 00:24:09,200
I thought I'd finally get to fight a dragon 
with my Dragon Slayer magic, but I guess not.

371
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,670
How lame!

372
00:24:10,670 --> 00:24:13,520
Although you're already captured inside it...

373
00:24:13,830 --> 00:24:16,510
Next time: Friendship 
will overcome the dead.

374
00:24:16,510 --> 00:24:18,390
I-I'm not captured!

375
00:24:18,390 --> 00:24:20,680
I'm... I'm riding it!

376
00:24:20,680 --> 00:24:23,810
Oh? Even though it's 
transportation? You're okay?

